703690f-a.text:
Clinton Street, at the N.w. corner of First Place, showing the Westminster Presbyterian Church organised on January 31, 1856. It was opened for services in a frame structure on this site in 1856. In 1867 this building was erected. In 1929 it had become the Norwegian's Sailor Church.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
